Ella Hall https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ella_Hall 0 Ella Hall (March 17, 1896 – September 3, 1981) was an American actress of the silent era. She appeared in 94 films between 1912 and 1933. She was the mother of both B-movie actress Ellen Hall and Richard Emory. Ella_Hall ( March_17_,_1896 – September_3 , 1981 ) was an_American_actress of the_silent_era .
